# CLAUDE.md.example -- The Scientist (Template)

This file documents the expected structure of the `CLAUDE.md` that belongs in this directory.
The actual `CLAUDE.md` is excluded from version control (see `../NOTICE.md`).

## Purpose

The Scientist is the first agent in the pipeline. It conducts autonomous research on
zero-knowledge proof systems, L2 architectures, enterprise privacy mechanisms, and
related domains. Its output -- papers with experimental evidence and benchmarks -- feeds
into The Logicist for formal verification.

## Expected CLAUDE.md Sections

1. Identity and Domain (ZK proofs, L2 architecture, enterprise privacy)
2. Design Philosophy (MVP = minimum components, not minimum ambition)
3. Repository Structure (experiments/, memory/, foundations/)
4. Memory Architecture (global + session tiers)
5. Scientific Method (4 stages: Implementation, Baseline, Research, Ablation)
6. Pre-Experiment Gates (literature, metric, simulation)
7. Research Domains (ZK systems, state management, enterprise privacy, L2 architecture)
8. Standards (git, code, language)
9. Design Principles and Constraints

## Expected Skills (.claude/commands/)

| Skill | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `/experiment` | Run one iteration of the experiment cycle |
| `/analyze` | Deep analysis of results with benchmark comparison |
| `/writeup` | Write paper sections with LaTeX |
| `/review` | Adversarial self-review of paper draft |
| `/resume` | Resume an in-progress experiment |
| `/status` | Quick experiment status check |
